 11/7/19 Chemnitz Spent the morn walk round talk to differ men special two veri fine L.H. chap from Egypt . Inspect the forward galley which is so terrif hot that men can hard bear the heat insid . The sea fair calm but plenti of white crest ? we notic sever sea gull ? the first bird sinc leav England . In the afternoon we had deck cricket go and some box bout and my veri pugilist friend Walker present one with his photograph . Jazz band and concert parti practic and danc and sing on the deck . An artilleryman weigh his issu today and found the bread to be 16 oz weight per loaf . The night much warmer and a lot of chap came on deck to sleep.
